data.description:
This 5-bedroom, 2-bathroom traditional home, nestled on 1.79 acres, offers a spacious open-concept floor plan. The focal point is a floor-to-ceiling brick fireplace, providing a cozy ambiance and stunning views. Ideal for animal enthusiasts, there's ample space for horses and goats. Located within 5 minutes of Copperas and 18 minutes of Fort Hood, it ensures convenience with just one traffic light to the closest gate.

Additionally, two versatile rooms can serve as a 6th and 7th bedroom or adaptable spaces for family, friends, or additional storage space. These rooms are equipped with heating and cooling, extending comfort throughout the home. The property includes two additional structures—one a metal building with two 18-foot barn doors for diverse activities and a smaller wooden shed for everyday items.

The highlight is an enchanting creek flowing through the back, creating a picturesque outdoor entertaining space. A large, covered patio with double-paned French doors enhances the seamless transition between indoor and outdoor living, providing a delightful setting for gatherings. This property is a unique opportunity for a harmonious blend of comfort, functionality, and natural beauty.
